      "content": "Critics argue that focusing on existential risk is speculative and distracts from the immediate, tangible harms AI already causes, such as job displacement and bias. They contend that overly broad regulation could stifle innovation, hindering the economic and scientific benefits AI offers. Moreover, some argue that the concept of a single, monolithic \"existential risk\" is overblown and lacks concrete evidence. Instead, they advocate for voluntary industry standards and a more agile, risk-based approach.",
      "source": "target",
